content.raw:
I still see several of these:
~~~
Exception AttributeError: AttributeError("'_DummyThread' object has no attribute '_Thread__block'",) in <module 'threading' from '/usr/lib/python2.7/threading.pyc'> ignored
~~~
I think it's a python issue though.

UPDATE: it's [python issue 14308](http://bugs.python.org/issue14308), and it's been fixed in python 2.7.4, but precise and quantal both use python 2.7.3, so we'll just have to live with it.
